  <properties>
    <title>Gallery Magick Image Core Library</title>
  </properties>
  <body>
    <section name="Gallery Magick Image Core Library">
      <subsection name="Introduction">
        <p>
          Gallery Image Processing Core is an image file processing library
          which <strong>executes</strong> commands (such as <code>gm convert</code> or <code>convert</code>) of
          either <a href="http://www.graphicsmagick.org/">GraphicsMagick</a>
          or <a href="http://www.imagemagick.org/">ImageMagick</a> to manipulate image files.
        </p>
        <p>
          This library provides the following components and utilities:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>GraphicsMagickCommand</strong> : encapsulation to execute
            <a href="http://www.graphicsmagick.org/">GraphicsMagick</a> commands such as <code>gm convert</code>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>GraphicsMagickCommandUtils</strong> : utility for simpler invocations on <strong>GraphicsMagickCommand</strong>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>ImageMagickCommand</strong> : encapsulation to execute
            <a href="http://www.imagemagick.org/">ImageMagick</a> commands such as <code>convert</code>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>ImageMagickCommandUtils</strong> : utility for simpler invocations on <strong>ImageMagickCommand</strong>.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          For more details and examples, please see <a href="../apidocs/index.html">API JavaDocs</a>
          and <a href="../xref-test/index.html">Unit Tests</a>.
        </p>
      </subsection>
    </section>

  </body>
